      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2023/01/Luka-Doncic-Drives-An-Apocalypse-HellFire-Jeep-6X6.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "For that kind of cash Doncic and others aren‚Äôt just getting a third axle. Apocalypse, which is based in Florida, loads the big, heavy Jeep with plenty of power via a supercharged 6.2-liter Hemi V8 like what you find in a Hellcat, only tuned for even better peformance. Claimed 0-60 acceleration is 3.7 seconds, so even though it might looking like a lumbering tank to many, it can scoot in a hurry.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2023/01/Luka-Doncic-Drives-An-Apocalypse-HellFire-Jeep-6X6-4.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "While the Jeep Gladiator does get a nice extension to accommodate the extra axle, it also benefits from a doubled towing capacity over factory spec. That‚Äôs right, owners can pull up to 12,000 lbs. which is useful, although we don‚Äôt see too many pulling a trailer.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2023/01/Luka-Doncic-Drives-An-Apocalypse-HellFire-Jeep-6X6-3.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "One other huge advantage with a 6x6 vehicle is additional traction in difficult terrain. While Doncic and many others use these rigs in urban environments, they‚Äôre good for at least some off-roading situations, although we question how well they‚Äôd handle certain technical trails. Still, the aggressive looks and the sheer size of these things always cause a ruckus no matter who‚Äôs driving them.",
